        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 5:14PM EDT by NWS Tallahassee FL</headline>
        <description>At 514 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Unionville, or near Tifton, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vanceville, Tift Airport, Enigma, Harding, Brookfield, Pinetta,
Tifton, and Unionville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
